From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0011/N] count_trailing_zeros: add CHERI cap-sized overload

HotSpot's `count_trailing_zeros<T>` template constrains T with
`std::is_integral<T>::value && sizeof(T) <= sizeof(uint64_t)`. On
CHERI/Morello purecap `uintptr_t == __intcap` is 16 bytes, so call
sites passing `uintptr_t`-typed values (oopStorage, regmask,
powerOfTwo, bitMap.inline) hit "no matching function for call to
count_trailing_zeros".

Add a CHERI-only overload that takes any 16-byte (cap-sized)
integral, casts to the 64-bit address representation, and forwards
to count_trailing_zeros_64. Cap metadata is irrelevant for bit
counting on an address.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0011)

--- a/src/hotspot/share/utilities/count_trailing_zeros.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/utilities/count_trailing_zeros.hpp
@@ -117,5 +117,17 @@ inline unsigned count_trailing_zeros(T x) {
          count_trailing_zeros_64(x);
 }

+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+// CHERI/Morello purecap: uintptr_t / uintcap_t is 16 bytes (128 bits), but
+// only the low 64 bits carry the address. Treat capability-sized values as
+// uint64_t for ctz purposes (cap metadata is not relevant to bit counting).
+template<typename T,
+         ENABLE_IF(sizeof(T) == sizeof(uintptr_t))>
+inline unsigned count_trailing_zeros(T x) {
+  assert(x != 0, "precondition");
+  return count_trailing_zeros_64(static_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<uintptr_t>(x)));
+}
+#endif
+

 #endif // SHARE_UTILITIES_COUNT_TRAILING_ZEROS_HPP
